user.biography: we browse through instagram and feature poems and writings we enjoy reading ✨

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by poets of instagram on September 19, 2021 tagging @thepacifiedsoulpoetry. May be an image of text that says '-ThePacifiedSouL- Happy with our memories, Happiest with you...'.

node.text:
life is not the same without you..⠀
(cr: @thepacifiedsoulpoetry)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by poets of instagram on September 19, 2021 tagging @n.m.sanchez. May be an image of text that says 'There are so many things I have wanted to tell you, and my heart breaks every time because I can't. Ν. M. Sanchez'.

node.text:

(cr: @n.m.sanchez)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by poets of instagram on September 19, 2021 tagging @chloefrayne. May be an image of text that says 'for me, love holds your name like it has never known another. -CHLOE FRAYNE.'.

node.text:
your name feels like the meaning of love 💓 ⠀
(cr: @chloefrayne)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by poets of instagram on September 19, 2021 tagging @langleav. May be an image of text that says 'If this is my heartache. then let it be mine to endure. Permit me to feel it in its entirety. Don't tell me how much of you I am allowed to love. -LANG LEAV (The Universe of Us)'.

node.text:
let me feel what I'm feeling 💔 ⠀
(cr: @langleav)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by poets of instagram on September 18, 2021 tagging @writealanche. May be an image of text that says 'Maybe the answer is within your heart, but you are wandering in wilderness.'.

node.text:
Maybe you're just a little lost at the moment,⠀
and that's ok. 🍁⠀
(cr: @writealanche)

Photo shared by poets of instagram on September 18, 2021 tagging @l.t.phoenixpoetry. May be an image of text that says 'he my in carried the weight of history, like င book his hands. and he stole my pages, chapters, my entire story, with just one smile. l.t. phoenix'.

Photo shared by poets of instagram on September 18, 2021 tagging @l.t.phoenixpoetry. May be an image of text that says 'You didn't delete our picture, and it took me forever and year to figure out why. You once said you can't let go of things. And I understand it now, because neither can I. -I still think ofyou LT. PHOENIX'.
Photo shared by poets of instagram on September 18, 2021 tagging @l.t.phoenixpoetry. May be an image of text that says 'We were a short-lived anthology of things no one else could read. LT.PHOENIX'.

Photo shared by poets of instagram on September 17, 2021 tagging @beilpoetry. May be an image of text that says 'sunshine, don't give up too soon this phase is a growing chapter that you and i can call cocoon a.b.'.

node.text:
The next stage of growth wouldn't be anything without all the work you're doing right now. ⠀
I am proud of you.⠀
(cr: @beilpoetry)
